This package contains the design inputs for the %#NewPhysicalArchModule#% . The %#NewPhysicalModule#% package is used to define the behaviors, specs, and architecture that is needed for the new module. The %#NewPhysicalArchModule#% Package provides the high level description for the module that needs to be incorporated into the detailed design. The package contains:
  1. Inputs Canvas
  2. Module Functions
  3. Design Specs and Reqs Analysis
  4. Use Cases
  5. Design Analysis
  6. Test Cases

The Design and Analysis is the package contains the block diagrams that describe the module's needed parts. There are two views of this show, the Block Definition Diagram that shows the tree of parts that make up the module and the Internal Block Diagram that defines how the blocks will interact.

The flow down from System to Subsystem to Design Specs is important to capture as the context for which the requirements were created should be considered when creating the design specs. The Design Spec and Requirements Analysis package is contains the requirements flow down for the %#NewPhysicalArchModule#%.

Use cases care created to describe the various uses of the module from the actors perspective. The Use Cases herein are specifically written to capture the behaviors of the %#NewPhysicalArchModule#% by capturing actor's goals. The use case process for %#NewPhysicalArchModule#% is recursively iterative decomposing use cases to break %#NewPhysicalArchModule#% into parts.

The functions package contains the breakdown of the subsystem functions into the functions that the module needs to fulfill. This package encapsulates a comprehensive set of functions that are derived from the broader system and subsystem functions, ensuring a seamless traceability and alignment with the overarching system architecture. Each function within this package is meticulously documented, highlighting its origin from system-level and subsystem-level requirements, and illustrating its role in fulfilling the module's operational capabilities.
This canvas is created to show the key design attributes for %#NewPhysicalArchModule#% which need to be considered when parts are selected to fulfill the functions.
<<New Physical Arch Module>> -Smart Req Analysis Diagram
The <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> Ports Table list the ports for interfacing with the <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> and a description of their needed function.

With each passing iteration additional functions are implemented through features. This diagram shows the generations at which the functions are planed to be implemented. Implementation is set based upon the MoSCoW Prioritization scale.
